    • EnumParameterKey

      public EnumParameterKey(@NotNull @NotNull Map<String,ParameterKey> keyMap, @NotNull @NotNull String name, boolean localOk, @Nullable E defaultValue, @Nullable @Nullable ParameterKey<?> dependsOn, boolean required, @NotNull @NotNull Class<E> enumClass)
      Creates an Enum parameter key.
      Parameters:
      keyMap - map of parameters.
      name - parameter name in the configuration file.
      localOk - true if the value can be overridden for an individual server or role.
      defaultValue - optional default value; null if this parameter has no default value.
      dependsOn - optional reference to a parameter that this parameter depends upon; null if this parameter does not depend upon another parameter.
      required - true if this parameter must have a value for an application to start.
      enumClass - the type of Enum represented by this parameter key.
